<br>
It was first that he wrote a letter to his sister Artemis, in hopes that they could get together for a hunt in the near future. After doing this, and quarreling with a nymph over the poor preparation of his morning nectar, Apollo dressed himself in a royal blue tunic adorned with a golden belt, his usual knee length cape, and golden sandels. Dismissing the nymphs for the remainder of the year, Apollo faded from the palace in a flurry of golden light.<br>
<br>
Appearing on Mt. Olympus only seconds later, his azure eyes bounced around. He heard voices comming from somewhere...ah the throneroom. Walking to the &quot;commons&quot; of the snow-capped wonder that is Olympus, a debonaire smile washed its away again onto Apollo's golden face. His golden, warm, sunlike aura increased slightly as he excitedly entered the room. His smile turning into a smirk as he addressed his family members.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hello to you all! 'Tis a wonder that I found you all here, I have just come out of hiatus from a small island off of Thasos and decided that my first appearance should be here. And what a wonderful decision that was...&quot; as he said this he embrassed his distant-grandmother, kissing her on the cheek.<br>
<br>
&quot;...for I bumped it all of you.&quot; he smiled, noding to his Uncle and kissing Demeter on the hand.<br>
<br>
&quot;How are things dearest aunt? I know that it is summer which seems to be your favorite season, everything being in full bloom.&quot; He smiled. It felt good to be home. <p>     *~*The Golden God*~*
